article.description: — Markquis Nowell had 17 points and 10 assists to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to a 78-50 win over Champion Christian College on Friday night.
article.headline: Nowell leads UALR past Champion Christian College 78-50
article.linkText: Nowell leads UALR past Champion Christian College 78-50
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- — Markquis Nowell had 17 points and 10 assists to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to a 78-50 win over Champion Christian College on Friday night. CJ White had 12 points for Arkansas-Little Rock (4-2). Xavier Legington had 13 points for the Tigers. Christian Chambers added eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
